<main class="about__page">
  <h1>About Us</h1>
  <p>
    At Oasis Games, we believe that choosing your next game shouldn't come down
    to a single number. Every player has different tastes, every reviewer brings
    a different perspective, and every game connects with people in its own way.
    That's why we built our platform around a simple idea: the best way to
    understand a game is to look at it from multiple viewpoints, not just one.
  </p>

  <p>
    Our team of reviewers forms the foundation of the site, playing and
    reviewing games using consistent standards to create a dependable baseline.
    Alongside our staff, established journalists and recognized gaming outlets
    can earn verified accounts, allowing readers to see their opinions
    separately from our own. We also encourage every player to join the
    conversation. Anyone can create an account, rate the games they've played,
    and write reviews that contribute to the community's overall perspective.
  </p>

  <p>
    Instead of blending every score into one average, Oasis Games breaks reviews
    into three groups: our staff, verified reviewers, and the community. This
    lets you see where opinions overlap and where they don't. A game that
    critics love but players find disappointing—or one that's overlooked by
    reviewers but embraced by the community—tells a much more interesting story
    than a single score ever could. Our goal is to provide the context behind
    the numbers so you can decide what matters most to you.
  </p>

  <p>
    Gaming is more diverse than ever, and so are the people who play it. We know
    that no review is completely objective, and that's okay. Rather than
    pretending there's one "correct" opinion, we believe transparency is the
    best way to help players make informed decisions. Whether you're looking for
    your next favorite indie title, the latest AAA release, or just curious
    about what everyone else thinks, Oasis Games is here to give you the
    clearest picture possible—so you can spend less time guessing and more time
    playing.
  </p>
</main>

